  "2026-07-12T11:57:15.410Z",maintainer-agent,"Census delta 2026-07-12: src/cli/main.ts 3369->3376/3400 (+7 effective, canonical normalizeLine method) — reset-on-entry seam for runtime-extension snapshot caches (pm-8fxc fix inside runPmCli). sdk/runtime.ts steady 3388/3400 after PR#524 (annotation kernel landed as NEW src/sdk/annotations.ts — precedent that new SDK domains can bypass the runtime.ts cap; see pm-usfg frontier note). Decomposition seam priorities unchanged."
notes[6]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-12T08:20:08.773Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-12 census refresh (same method: static-quality-gate normalizeLine over src/**/*.ts, cap 3400). Delta vs the 07-11 body census:\n- sdk/runtime.ts 3236 -> 3388 (99.6% of cap, 12 effective lines of headroom) — now the #1 at-risk file, overtaking main.ts (3369, unchanged). Growth is the SDK-first slices themselves: PR#512 (plan), PR#517 (ranked atomic selection), PR#520 (schema boundaries) all land action surface here.\n- SEQUENCING CONSEQUENCE: pm-3mna S1 (next SDK slice, current recommended frontier) cannot merge without blowing the gate. The runtime.ts seam owned here (per-domain action tables + shared dispatch kernel, runAction semantics-oracle preserved) must land FIRST — either as a standalone prep PR or as 3mna S1's first commit. Coordination note posted on pm-usfg.\n- context.ts crossed 2000 (2011) — watch, not owned here (context belongs to pm-oslr slice relief first).\n- create.ts 2851->2789, update.ts 2758->2697 (PR#523 relief); register-mutation 3037, completion 2818 (+5/+9 noise); search.ts/loader.ts/extension.ts/validate.ts unchanged.\n- Files >=3000: 7; >=2000: 17. Priority bumped 2->1 on the strength of the runtime.ts headroom."
  "2026-07-12T08:43:58.354Z",codex-root,"Execution rule from user escalation (23rd recurrence): this active delivery lane must not stop at partial implementation, local verification, commit, PR creation, pending checks, or pending bot review. Continue through the requested green reviewed PR, merge, merged-head/release/Sentry/telemetry proof, tracker closure, claim release, and return to main; only a genuine exhausted blocker permits stopping."
  "2026-07-12T19:14:59.833Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-12 directive recurrence (too-many/too-long, document-only): the folder-density half is now owned by sibling pm-kb5h (source-tree directory fan-out, 6-tranche blueprint). Fence: yh8r = intra-file effective-LOC decomposition of near-cap files; kb5h = inter-file directory regrouping. Any physical move of a yh8r target file happens WITH its yh8r split (or its usfg slice), never as a standalone kb5h move — one migration per file. LOC census unchanged from this morning's note (runtime.ts 3388 = #1 at-risk)."
  "2026-07-13T09:49:54.816Z",maintainer-agent,"Census refresh 2026-07-13 (review pass #78, gate-normalized LOC vs 3400 cap): main.ts 3386 (99.6% — 14 lines of headroom, next commander registration will likely breach), sdk/runtime.ts 3367 (99.0%), core/extensions/loader.ts 3312 (97.4%), commands/extension.ts 3239 (95.3%), register-mutation.ts 3066 (90.2%), commands/validate.ts 3052 (89.8%). main.ts is now the most urgent seam (was runtime.ts at pass #71). Raw wc -l overcounts (~300 lines/file) — always measure via normalizeLine from scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs."
  "2026-07-13T14:24:31.363Z",maintainer-agent,"LOC census refresh 2026-07-13 (post PR#543, gate-normalized vs 3400 cap): src/cli/main.ts 3386 (headroom 14, unchanged — still the most urgent seam); src/sdk/runtime.ts 3365 (headroom 35 — grew again via PR#543 import rerouting and is now the second-tightest seam; each SDK promotion slice adds imports/exports here, so the pm-usfg slices 3mna/oxrw/4a7m/oslr will keep pressing it — runtime.ts partition should precede or accompany the next slice); src/cli/commands/search.ts 3359 (headroom 41, unchanged). No gate violations; never raise the cap."
  "2026-07-15T19:11:25.602Z",maintainer-agent,"LOC census refresh 2026-07-15 (review pass #89, post PR#568, gate-normalized vs 3400 cap): src/sdk/runtime.ts 3400 — HEADROOM ZERO, the gate is saturated; the next non-comment line added anywhere in the file fails quality:static. main.ts 3377 (headroom 23), search.ts 3359 (41, unchanged), sdk/extension.ts 3349 (51), extensions/loader.ts 3312 (88, unchanged), governance/validate.ts 3103, register-mutation.ts 3074. Consequence for sequencing: the runtime.ts partition can no longer \"precede or accompany\" the next pm-usfg slice — it must land FIRST, since pm-oslr (execution/diagnostics) and pm-ju83 (relationship registry, current pm-next recommended) both add runtime.ts exports/imports. No gate violations today; never raise the cap."
files[1]{path,scope,note}:
  scripts/release/sdk-import-boundary-baseline.json,project,removed annotation command private-core boundary entries
body: "## Why (2026-07-11 maintainer directive: too many too-long files by effective LOC; document-only pass)\nEffective-LOC census (non-blank, non-comment; gate counts the same way since PR#506, cap 3400):\nmain.ts 3369 (99%) · search.ts 3330 (jt3b) · extensions/loader.ts 3312 · commands/extension.ts 3239 · sdk/runtime.ts 3236 · validate.ts 3052 (oxrw) · register-mutation.ts 3032 · create.ts 2851 · completion.ts 2809 · update.ts 2758 · extension/scaffold.ts 2739 · test.ts 2713 (oslr) · health.ts 2460 (oxrw) · telemetry/runtime.ts 2366 · contracts.ts 2358 · plan.ts 2095 (je50).\nThe old LOC growth watch (pm-k1im) and main.ts items (pm-6c3h, pm-sh6o) are closed; nothing OPEN owns the infrastructure files, and main.ts is one feature away from failing the gate.\n\n## Ownership fences (never double-file)\n- search.ts → pm-jt3b (query-parser + inline-field split already scoped).\n- Command files in the promotion partition get FIRST relief from their SDK slice (validate/health → pm-oxrw, schema/config/profile/init → pm-3mna, plan → pm-je50, test/context → pm-oslr, annotations → pm-zwpp, history-maintenance → pm-4a7m); decompose only the presentation remainder if still near cap afterwards.\n- THIS item owns the files outside that partition: main.ts, core/extensions/loader.ts, sdk/runtime.ts, cli/register-mutation.ts, cli/commands/completion.ts (+ commands/extension.ts + scaffold.ts if their slice relief is insufficient).\n\n## Split seams (follow the PR#396 split playbook: extract at same call position, public surface byte-identical)\n- main.ts → continue the pm-6c3h/pm-sh6o per-command-registration extraction; bootstrap/help/global-flag blocks are self-contained.\n- loader.ts → manifest-parse / activation / sandbox-boundary seams (version-compat already extracted, pm-sjea precedent).\n- sdk/runtime.ts → per-domain action tables + shared dispatch kernel (keeps runAction semantics-oracle role intact).\n- register-mutation.ts → per-mutation registration modules mirroring commands/index.ts layout.\n- completion.ts → data tables (flag strings per shell) out of logic; tables are generated-ish and cheap to isolate."
